         <abstract>
            <p>The purpose of this paper is to explain how to compute the function $\Omega$ which interpolates values of a function of one variable $f(x)$ at $n$ distinct points $x_1 &lt; x_2 &lt; \cdots &lt; x_{n-1} &lt; x_n$, and which, whenever $\|f^{(k)}\|_\infty$ is bounded and the value of the bound is unknown, provides the smallest possible value of $B(x)$ in the error bound $$|f(x) - \Omega(x)| \leqslant B(x)\|f^{(k)}\|_\infty.$$</p>
